00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,200
Previously on jericho all right,it looks 
like the explosion came from the west,maybe denver. 

2
00:00:01,220 --> 00:00:01,790
Are we under attack ? 

3
00:00:01,810 --> 00:00:02,590
This could've been a test. 

4
00:00:02,610 --> 00:00:03,990
Could've been an accident. 

5
00:00:04,010 --> 00:00:08,330
Look,I know you're telling people it was 
an accident,but if it was an attack,sheriff,

6
00:00:08,360 --> 00:00:12,800
and there's chaos out there,you might not want the 
wrong people knowing that jericho is still here. 

7
00:00:12,830 --> 00:00:17,410
Dale turner's mother died 
tonight in another explosion. 

8
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:18,550
Atlanta. 

9
00:00:18,570 --> 00:00:20,240
Oh,my god. 

10
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:22,940
Won't the rain clear the radiation out of the air ? 

11
00:00:22,960 --> 00:00:24,930
Yes,and bring it straight down on jericho. 

12
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:26,580
A direct,concentrated hit. 

13
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,590
Anyone exposed too long...

14
00:00:28,620 --> 00:00:31,510
how do you know about radiation,mr. Hawkins ? 

15
00:00:32,180 --> 00:00:33,090
Stanley. 

16
00:00:33,110 --> 00:00:34,500
No,hey ! 

17
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:36,520
Stanley,don't touch her. 

18
00:00:37,510 --> 00:00:39,500
How do you know the rain's radioactive ? 

19
00:00:39,520 --> 00:00:40,740
Denver's pretty far away. 

20
00:00:40,760 --> 00:00:43,260
Well,we don't know how many bombs there were. 

21
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:47,660
oh,my god. 

22
00:00:47,690 --> 00:00:48,800
We got something ! 

23
00:00:48,860 --> 00:00:50,320
Are they just reporting it or are they behind it ? 

24
00:00:50,350 --> 00:00:51,550
Maybe we're being invaded. 

25
00:00:51,570 --> 00:00:54,100
If this country is at war,we need to know it. 

26
00:00:54,120 --> 00:00:56,610
More than electricity or food,
this town needs information. 

27
00:00:56,650 --> 00:00:57,890
We can't just sit here in the dark. 

28
00:00:57,920 --> 00:00:58,820
He's right. 

29
00:00:58,830 --> 00:01:00,290
Makes us too vulnerable. 

30
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:03,230
We could organize a group of people,
send them out in every direction. 

31
00:01:03,260 --> 00:01:04,760
The four horsemen of the apocalypse. 

32
00:01:04,790 --> 00:01:06,270
Let's hope not. 

33
00:01:07,730 --> 00:01:12,050
4 days after the bombs

34
00:01:12,110 --> 00:01:18,240
1 day after the fallout has cleared

35
00:01:33,970 --> 00:01:35,680
I'm telling you,it's the midwest. 

36
00:01:35,710 --> 00:01:37,940
From the skyline,I'm thinking cincinnati. 

37
00:01:37,970 --> 00:01:41,050
I wish we could read the license plates. 

38
00:01:42,490 --> 00:01:45,490
let's make cincinnati a question mark. 

39
00:02:03,460 --> 00:02:04,130
Jake. 

40
00:02:04,130 --> 00:02:05,700
Hey,stanley. 
Hey,bonnie. 

41
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:06,990
Anything new ? 

42
00:02:07,110 --> 00:02:08,920
No,not since yesterday. 

43
00:02:08,950 --> 00:02:11,860
Shep and gray should have been back by now. 

44
00:02:11,980 --> 00:02:16,040
Our radios went silent about 50 miles out. 

45
00:02:17,650 --> 00:02:22,170
God,it makes you wonder what 
happened to whoever shot this. 

46
00:02:22,730 --> 00:02:26,420
I think that might have been 
the last thing they ever saw. 

47
00:02:44,990 --> 00:02:46,520
the generator's running out of gas. 

48
00:02:46,540 --> 00:02:48,550
We're going to lose the tv. 

49
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,950
I'll take care of it. 

50
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:52,120
How can you ? 

51
00:02:52,170 --> 00:02:55,220
Gas pumps don't work at the 
station with the power down. 

52
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:57,820
Look,I don't want you to worry. 

53
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:05,360
Sorry,folks. 

54
00:03:05,390 --> 00:03:06,720
We're closing early tonight. 

55
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:08,400
Take a flashlight,it's dark out there. 

56
00:03:08,420 --> 00:03:09,780
What ? It's only 9:30. 

57
00:03:09,810 --> 00:03:11,440
You heard her,let's move it,folks. 

58
00:03:11,460 --> 00:03:12,740
Time to go home. 

59
00:03:12,740 --> 00:03:14,360
Let's move it out. 

60
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:27,580
Is the generator out ? 

61
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:29,480
No,out of booze. 

62
00:03:30,170 --> 00:03:31,510
any more images ? 

63
00:03:31,540 --> 00:03:33,170
No,just the same loop. 

64
00:03:33,190 --> 00:03:35,150
Come on,I'll walk you home. 

65
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,580
Where do you live ? 

66
00:03:37,110 --> 00:03:38,670
That way. 

67
00:03:40,460 --> 00:03:44,320
So is it weird being home after so long ? 

68
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,680
A little bit. 

69
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:49,430
I still can't get used to bailey's 
without the mechanical bull. 

70
00:03:49,690 --> 00:03:51,960
Stanley must have cried when they took that out. 

71
00:03:51,990 --> 00:03:53,820
He had the record. 

72
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:57,470
When did the pizza garden 
become the cyberjolt cafe ? 

73
00:03:57,500 --> 00:04:00,370
Oh,when the health department 
shut down the pizza garden. 

74
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,060
What ?  ! 

75
00:04:01,090 --> 00:04:02,650
Oh,don't tell me you liked the pizza garden. 

76
00:04:02,670 --> 00:04:06,270
I used to work there washing dishes. 

77
00:04:06,290 --> 00:04:09,520
Oh,you must not have done a very good job. 

78
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:13,510
that came from the alley. 

79
00:04:27,830 --> 00:04:30,080
It's the pharmacy. 

80
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:39,420
Why don't you go get some help ? 

81
00:05:07,330 --> 00:05:09,390
help...

82
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:17,260
sync:fisherchen, hoodman

83
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:24,150
YDY proudly presents

84
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,780
Jake. 

85
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:32,250
Who is he ? 

86
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:32,940
I don't know. 

87
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,040
Help me get him out of here. 

88
00:05:34,060 --> 00:05:35,750
Not without gloves or a hazmat suit. 

89
00:05:35,770 --> 00:05:38,210
We got to get him to a doctor,now. 

90
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:43,490
is that radiation sickness ? 

91
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:45,800
I think it might be. 

92
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,030
Heather,heather. 

93
00:05:50,060 --> 00:05:51,270
Get her out. 
Okay. 

94
00:05:51,310 --> 00:05:52,290
Let's go. 

95
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:54,660
Come on,bill,let's go. 

96
00:05:54,730 --> 00:05:56,330
Help us pick him up. 
I'm not touching him. 

97
00:05:56,350 --> 00:05:58,360
No way. Not me. He could be contagious. 

98
00:05:58,380 --> 00:06:00,730
He's not contagious,bill. 

99
00:06:00,870 --> 00:06:02,070
I'm sorry,stanley. 

100
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:05,720
What if it was me lying here,bill ? 
Would you walk away then ? 

101
00:06:05,910 --> 00:06:08,970
We could get sick touching that guy. 

102
00:06:09,390 --> 00:06:10,830
It's not like with you,stanley. 

103
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:12,960
We don't even know who this guy is. 

104
00:06:12,990 --> 00:06:16,220
I just stopped by bailey's to check on the tv signal. 

105
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:17,860
Can't you cut your husband some slack ? 

106
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:19,970
And that took three hours ? 

107
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:22,650
I was only there for,like,an hour. 

108
00:06:22,670 --> 00:06:25,660
We're in a state of emergency,eric. 

109
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:27,430
I'm aware of that,april. 

110
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:30,170
Dr. Peterson's gone to kansas city 
to look for his daughter. 

111
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:32,760
And dr. Hoder's worked the last 24 hours. 
Well,I am here now. 

112
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:36,460
What do you want from me ? 
And you...decided to go have a beer. 

113
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:40,920
I've got a baby on a ventilator and 
the generator is almost out of gas. 

114
00:06:40,940 --> 00:06:43,360
Well,don't you have a hand pump ? 

115
00:06:44,620 --> 00:06:45,830
Who'd pump it ? 

116
00:06:45,850 --> 00:06:47,970
Out of the way. 

117
00:06:48,110 --> 00:06:49,350
Out of the way ! 

118
00:06:49,380 --> 00:06:51,100
April,he's having trouble breathing. 

119
00:06:51,130 --> 00:06:53,100
Get him in room three. 

120
00:07:18,370 --> 00:07:19,970
who is that ? 

121
00:07:19,990 --> 00:07:21,840
Who's in there ? 

122
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:25,330
Hello ? 

123
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:30,860
Who is that ? 

124
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:34,380
it's just me,mrs. Leigh. 

125
00:07:34,410 --> 00:07:36,850
Oh,dale. 

126
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:39,440
What are you up to ? You scared me to death. 

127
00:07:39,470 --> 00:07:40,900
It was supposed to be a surprise. 

128
00:07:40,930 --> 00:07:42,510
What ? 

129
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:52,810
where did you get all this ? 

130
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:54,340
The train that never showed up. 

131
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,100
It smashed into a car. 

132
00:07:55,130 --> 00:07:56,900
There's a ton of food just sitting on it. 

133
00:07:56,930 --> 00:07:59,880
It's just about five miles outside of town. 

134
00:08:00,060 --> 00:08:02,630
Well,we can't just take it,it's not ours. 

135
00:08:02,650 --> 00:08:04,680
Not all of it,anyway. 

136
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:06,680
The town took your food. 

137
00:08:07,250 --> 00:08:09,400
Well,it was an emergency. 

138
00:08:09,430 --> 00:08:11,710
And so is this. 

139
00:08:12,530 --> 00:08:14,690
The hell with them. 

140
00:08:22,110 --> 00:08:23,320
Who is this man ? 

141
00:08:23,340 --> 00:08:25,240
Anyone recognize him ? 

142
00:08:25,610 --> 00:08:27,520
Not so far. 

143
00:08:28,420 --> 00:08:29,980
Those burns...

144
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:32,400
does that mean that he was close to the blast ? 

145
00:08:32,430 --> 00:08:34,090
Why'd he come to jericho ? 

146
00:08:34,110 --> 00:08:35,450
It's a hell of a way from denver. 

147
00:08:35,470 --> 00:08:37,550
Maybe he's related to someone in town. 

148
00:08:37,570 --> 00:08:40,100
Then why'd he break into the pharmacy ? 

149
00:08:40,810 --> 00:08:41,700
any I. D.  ? 

150
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:43,350
No,just some keys. 

151
00:08:43,370 --> 00:08:45,640
He doesn't even have a wallet. 

152
00:08:49,780 --> 00:08:50,820
is he going to be okay ? 

153
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,280
Depends on the dose that he got. 

154
00:08:56,460 --> 00:08:58,670
son,you and stanley should go wash up. 

155
00:08:58,690 --> 00:09:00,250
Those clothes might still be contaminated. 

156
00:09:00,270 --> 00:09:02,110
There's a shower down the hall. 

157
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,070
dad. 

158
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,740
We got another situation. 

159
00:09:19,770 --> 00:09:22,650
There's not much more gas in the generator here. 

160
00:09:22,740 --> 00:09:24,440
Bailey's tavern went dark tonight. 

161
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:30,630
That was the only satellite dish in town getting 
a signal,our only link to the outside world. 

162
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:31,790
you okay ? 

163
00:09:31,830 --> 00:09:32,850
Yeah. 

164
00:09:32,890 --> 00:09:36,190
We're going to have to get people 
to siphon gas out of their cars. 

165
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:38,010
What if more come ? 

166
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:40,390
There's not enough gas to keep the 
clinics going for all of them. 

167
00:09:40,420 --> 00:09:42,070
You saying we ought to turn them away ? 

168
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:44,780
No,I'm saying we have limited resources. 

169
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:48,010
Well,for right now,let's just 
get as much gas as we can. 

170
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:49,550
Some of the nurses are spooked. 

171
00:09:49,570 --> 00:09:51,440
They're worried about contamination. 

172
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:54,220
Honey,I'll do anything I can to help you. 

173
00:09:55,970 --> 00:10:01,800
If you could,keep an eye on this baby,
then I could see to the other patients. 

174
00:10:01,830 --> 00:10:03,380
Sure. 

175
00:10:03,630 --> 00:10:05,580
I hope to god the power doesn't go. 

176
00:10:05,610 --> 00:10:10,140
Look,we'll do everything we can,until we can't. 

177
00:10:34,190 --> 00:10:37,390
menphis

178
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:41,150
dad,it's sam. 

179
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:42,880
vacations

180
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:47,830
dad,I'm thirsty,are you in there ? 

181
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:49,710
Any word from shep or gray ? 

182
00:10:49,740 --> 00:10:50,600
No,mayor. 

183
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:52,100
Still can't get 'em on the radio. 

184
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:55,550
Maybe they got captured by those tanks stanley saw. 

185
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:58,980
Those tanks are probably just national guard okay ? 

186
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,700
So...you don't know that. 

187
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:02,640
They could be...shh. 

188
00:11:05,470 --> 00:11:07,690
They could be china,they could be iran. 

189
00:11:07,710 --> 00:11:10,960
Al qaeda,north korea...anybody who hates us. 

190
00:11:10,980 --> 00:11:14,650
They could be coming here and 
what's our line of defense ? 

191
00:11:16,490 --> 00:11:18,670
You're looking at it. 

192
00:11:24,140 --> 00:11:25,430
Jake ? 

193
00:11:29,540 --> 00:11:31,540
Had to take a shower. 

194
00:11:31,570 --> 00:11:32,200
Go ahead. 

195
00:11:32,230 --> 00:11:35,360
No,i I did; I just took a shower. 

196
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:38,030
Oh,right. 

197
00:11:38,150 --> 00:11:40,070
So what's up ? 

198
00:11:40,850 --> 00:11:42,350
I...

199
00:11:42,710 --> 00:11:46,730
April said that the medical center was 
running low on gasoline for the generator,

200
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:51,560
and it occurred to me that if we had a length of 
hose and a funnel,we could siphon gas out of our cars. 

201
00:11:51,580 --> 00:11:55,670
Then it occurred to me there's all that gas 
in the tanks at murthy's gas station

202
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:59,430
and if we could get enough suction 
we could get all the gas we wanted...

203
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:02,180
would a water pump do it ? 

204
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,870
Bonnie. 

205
00:12:16,830 --> 00:12:19,270
This could be my brother. 

206
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:20,860
Is this how they die ? 

207
00:12:20,890 --> 00:12:22,730
No. Stanley didn't get it this bad. 

208
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:24,400
He could still got cancer. 

209
00:12:24,430 --> 00:12:26,430
No,we don't know that. 

210
00:12:26,910 --> 00:12:28,190
Listen. 

211
00:12:28,430 --> 00:12:31,610
Don't worry about me,I'll be fine. 

212
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:36,630
Take care of him. 

213
00:12:44,190 --> 00:12:47,300
I'm going to have to put him on a 
ventilator,it'll use up power but...

214
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:50,370
but the baby has the better chance for 
survival,save the generator for the baby. 

215
00:12:50,390 --> 00:12:52,530
Hey,hey,hey,what about him ? 

216
00:12:52,830 --> 00:12:54,240
Give him something for the pain. 

217
00:12:54,250 --> 00:12:55,060
Keep him comfortable. 

218
00:12:55,090 --> 00:12:56,330
Sit back and watch him die. 

219
00:12:56,340 --> 00:12:59,710
Well,I don't like it,jake,but that's the 
most rational option we have right now. 

220
00:12:59,730 --> 00:13:02,130
Unless you can think of something better. 

221
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,340
Will your generator last until morning ? 

222
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,660
I think so. 

223
00:13:07,670 --> 00:13:09,280
All right,give me until then. 

224
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:19,590
can you tell me your name ? 

225
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:23,400
victor. 

226
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:25,220
Miller. 

227
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:26,980
Victor. 

228
00:13:27,290 --> 00:13:29,200
Victor,you're in a medical clinic. 

229
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:31,030
Okay,we're going to take care of you. 

230
00:13:31,070 --> 00:13:32,630
No,no. 

231
00:13:34,030 --> 00:13:36,030
They're coming. 

232
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:41,180
They're coming. 

233
00:13:58,490 --> 00:14:01,420
So how long do you think he'll be unconscious ? 

234
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:03,280
Could be a long time. 

235
00:14:03,310 --> 00:14:05,620
If he ever wakes up again. 

236
00:14:05,670 --> 00:14:07,360
Who are "they" ? 

237
00:14:07,380 --> 00:14:08,720
Who's coming ? 

238
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:12,680
Well,maybe he saw passengers 
from one of those planes. 

239
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:14,330
He could've meant terrorists. 

240
00:14:14,350 --> 00:14:17,290
Unless he wakes up,we don't know 
what kind of danger were in. 

241
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:21,430
For right now,hire as many deputies 
as you can,use them to help you get gas. 

242
00:14:21,430 --> 00:14:22,990
Clinic's running low. 

243
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:25,240
But it's not my gas,it belongs to noraco. 

244
00:14:25,260 --> 00:14:26,680
It's no use to anyone,mr. Murthy. 

245
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:28,680
Without electricity,the pumps don't even work. 

246
00:14:28,700 --> 00:14:30,960
And we'll leave you an I. O. U. For the 500 gallons. 

247
00:14:30,980 --> 00:14:32,090
I could be fired. 

248
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:34,630
With all due respect,who's going to fire you ? 

249
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:37,420
It's a different world now,mr. Murthy. 

250
00:14:39,510 --> 00:14:40,560
All right,let's get them open. 

251
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:43,160
Stanley will be here any second. 

252
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:53,300
They're never coming back. 

253
00:14:53,460 --> 00:14:55,740
The district manager,any of them. 

254
00:14:56,370 --> 00:14:57,990
Are they ? 

255
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,290
No. 

256
00:15:04,790 --> 00:15:09,440
Shortly after my mother died,
my husband was transferred to st. Louis. 

257
00:15:09,460 --> 00:15:12,170
It was hard to leave memphis,
because it was our home. 

258
00:15:12,190 --> 00:15:16,280
But eventually we learned to love it. 

259
00:15:16,380 --> 00:15:18,380
How did your mother die ? 

260
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:21,070
M. S. 

261
00:15:21,220 --> 00:15:24,500
Aly,what area of st. Louis are we from ? 

262
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:25,750
Kirkwood. 
Which is where ? 

263
00:15:25,770 --> 00:15:26,820
Near powder valley. 

264
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:28,880
Lots of hiking,trails and nature. 

265
00:15:28,900 --> 00:15:30,900
